The Chronicle Thupeyo Muleya, Beitbridge Bureau There is a standoff between the police and a suspected armed robber in Dulivhadzimu suburbs, Beitbridge. <img class="size-full wp-image-515252" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/10/IMG-20201015-WA0045.jpg" alt="" width="273" height="364" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/10/IMG-20201015-WA0045.jpg 273w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/10/IMG-20201015-WA0045-270x360.jpg 270w" sizes="(max-width: 273px) 100vw, 273px" /> The house where there is a standoff, police have cordoned off the area The suspect is reported to have evaded an early arrest yesterday before being tracked to a house where he has locked himself and has been firing wild shots since 1 am. The police have surrounded the house.Â One police source said they are giving him room to finish up his ammunition so they safely arrest him. Additional special tactical team members have been dispatched from Bulawayo. 